The deposed Emir of Kano, Sanusi Lamido Sanusi, few miutes ago regained his freedom from where he was banished in Awe local government of Nasarawa state.   One of his counsel, Abdulrasheed Murtala confirmed to LEADERSHIP WEEKEND that he had just been released from confinement. According to him, the order of court has been fully obeyed by the relevant parties.    